mistral.reason: Sextans B is a galaxy, not an epoch. An epoch refers to a specific point in time or a period of time, while Sextans B is a physical object located approximately 4.44 million light years away from Earth and within the Local Group of galaxies.

gemma2.reason: It states a galaxy, Sextans B, is an epoch. Epochs refer to specific points or periods in time, often used in astronomical studies. Galaxies are celestial objects, not units of time.

llama3.1.reason: It's mentioned as a galaxy with an apparent magnitude of 11.9, located either within the Local Group or just beyond it, and having five planetary nebulae discovered in it, which are all characteristics of a celestial body, not an epoch.
